OUR PHILOSOPHY Everything we need for our survival and well-being on Planet Earth depends on our natural and social environments.  Humans and nature can and should exist in productive harmony, which is why businesses and people should do more than just make money and amass wealth:  they should act in ways that improve the world while making money.  20th Century capitalism operated under two flawed assumptions. First, Planet Earth has unlimited resources. Second, individuals can and should amass unlimited wealth for their own benefit.  As the world is awakening in the 21st Century, both of these assumptions are proving to be unsustainable. Finance is a key lever for change and can play a major role in shaping a more sustainable future. Supraxis sees sustainable finance as a powerful tool to address the issues humanity faces in the 21st Century including environmental degradation, natural resource depletion, climate change, and social inequality.

Founded in Berkeley, California, Taxnexus is a financial technology service for the cannabis industry that solves real-world tax compliance problems for recreational and medical cannabis taxpayers and regulators. Taxnexus is the first global tax management software solution aimed to help cannabis industry participants (taxpayers) become and remain compliant with all state, county, and local jurisdictional cannabis excise and sales and use taxes. Cannabis POS and ERP software developers can adapt their existing, cloud-based offerings to Taxnexus API for cannabis businesses to calculate state, county and local excise taxes, track and store all tax data, and file monthly cannabis tax returns in an easy, inexpensive and compliant manner. Taxnexus API creates a financial chain of custody from the cannabis taxpayer to the state treasury. What is next? Full Description: Simultaneously managing complex budgets, maintaining an efficient worksite, and meeting OSHA standards is no easy feat on a construction project. With multiple vendors constantly stepping in and out of your site, the endless interruptions reduce worker productivity and create safety hazards. But what if you could boost your jobsite productivity, maintain strict safety standards, and increase your revenue in the process? To help you radically simplify your workflow, our founders created Jobsite365 — the safer, more efficient jobsite solution. Through our cutting-edge application, general contractors can give vendors and subcontractors quick and easy access to sub-lists without interruption, reducing the number of distractions you and your workers face. GCs and sub-contractors can request and compare quotes from multiple vendors, allowing you to shop for the best deal and improve your bottom line. Vendors on the app can receive sub-lists, send quotes for equipment and supplies, and coordinate deliveries with one another. These features not only reduce your administrative burden, but they also minimize the number of people on your construction site at any given time. If you are a general contractor, sub-contractor, or vendor looking to improve the efficiency of making professional connections while simplifying your workday, sign up for the Jobsite365 marketplace today: https://www.jobsite365.com/
